    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Looks like GitHub does some additional rendering if it's just a LICENSE file, see https://github.com/PowerShell/PSReadLine/blob/master/LICENSE\r\n\r\nHowever, the LICENSE.txt is actually included in the package so keeping .txt also makes sense.  Since Windows relies on extensions, that file will open, by default, in Notepad rather than being asked for the app to open it.\r\n\r\nSeems like GitHub should support the .txt extension.",
